ional muster, Lessig and Seligman explain how some might. They expose correctable weaknesses in the system, including one that could be corrected only by the Supreme Court. Any strategy aimed at hacking a presidential election is a threat to democracy. This book is a clarion call to shore up the insecure system for electing the president before American democracy is forever compromised.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aElection lawzUnited States. 0aPresidentszUnited StatesxElection. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aSeligman, Matthew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074979340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300277524?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300277524423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300277524/original  a978-3-11-074979-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles